This paper discusses the incentives of AI agents to allow themselves to be switched off, which falls under the category of AI safety and control. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing a game between a human and a robot, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential risks of misbehaving AI systems, which could fall under computer security (cs.CR) or systems and control (cs.SY).
